description.narrative: UNICEF innovatively leveraged GPE funds as an entry point for the development of a national social protection system. Working with the Ministry of Social Affairs, unconditional cash assistance was provided to1400 vulnerable families, as a critical shock-responsive measure to address the effects of COVID-19. Drawing on evidence generated from the MICs, MPI, MODA and routine data systems, UNICEF reinforced advocacy for investments for children resulting in renewed engagement by national authorities and donors to increase allocations for children in key sectors. Capacity development of key technicians in results-based management is positioned to enhance future local planning and budgeting activities. | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/01/2022
